    "description_long": "This object consists of a dark wooden coffin with a partially open lid, accompanied by four wooden crosses of varying sizes and shapes. The coffin is hexagonal and appears to be constructed from planks, with a simple, rustic finish. The interior of the coffin is visible and appears empty, with the lid propped open. The four crosses are made from rough, unpolished wood and are positioned upright, likely intended as grave markers. The overall appearance is somber and utilitarian, evoking a traditional graveyard setting. There are no visible inscriptions or decorative elements on either the coffin or the crosses.",
